HOUSE BILL 1360
M3, R1 5lr1567
By: Delegates Qi, Acevero, Cardin, Fair, Guyton, Palakovich Carr, Ruth, Spiegel,
Vogel, Wims, and Woorman
Introduced and read first time: February 7, 2025
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Environment – Road Salt – Outdoor Storage
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting certain persons from storing road salt uncovered outdoors;
4 requiring the Department of the Environment to adopt regulations to establish
5 proper outdoor storage requirements for road salt and penalties for noncompliance;
6 and generally relating to the outdoor storage of road salt.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Environment
9 Section 9–2302
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2014 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Environment
15 9–2302.
16 (A) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO AN ENTITY COVERED BY A SALT
17 MANAGEMENT PLAN UNDER A FEDERAL PERMIT.
18 (B) A PERSON MAY NOT STORE ROAD SALT UNCOVERED OUTDOORS.
19 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO ESTABLISH:
20 (1) PROPER OUTDOOR STORAGE REQUIREMENTS FOR ROAD SALT;
21 AND
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
