2 HOUSE BILL 1360
1 (2) PENALTIES AND REMEDIATION REQUIREMENTS FOR FAILURE TO
2 COMPLY WITH THE REGULATIONS.
3 (D) A PERSON WHO STORES ROAD SALT OUTDOORS SHALL ENSURE THE
4 STORAGE IS COMPLIANT WITH THE REGULATIONS ADOPTED BY THE DEPARTMENT
5 UNDER THIS SECTION.
6 (E) A COUNTY STORMWATER MANAGEMENT AUTHORITY IN COORDINATION
7 WITH THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ENFORCE THIS SECTION.
8 (F) NOTHING IN THIS SECTION SHALL BE CONSTRUED TO ALTER, PREEMPT,
9 OR OTHERWISE RELIEVE LIABILITY FOR THE DISCHARGE OF ROAD SALT INTO
10 WATERS OF THE STATE OR THE STATE’S ENFORCEMENT AUTHORITY UNDER THE
11 FEDERAL CLEAN WATER ACT.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
13 October 1, 2025.

